        "chapter_title": "Introduction",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.1",
            "summary": "This supervisory statement is of interest to UK solo insurance firms within the scope of Solvency II that carry out nonlife business and the Society of Lloyd’s, in respect of each of their Syndicates ",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2018"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.2",
            "summary": "This statement sets out the Prudential Regulation Authority’s (PRA’s) expectations of how firms should identify and manage all risks to which their business could be exposed over the long term, as wel",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2018"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.3",
            "summary": "In December 2013, the PRA issued SS4/131 which set out the PRA’s approach to firms’ development of their forward looking assessment of own risks, based on the Own Risk and Solvency Assessment (ORSA) p",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2018"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.4",
            "summary": "This statement is consistent with SS4/13 on capturing all known risks in a firm’s forward looking assessment, or ORSA, and sets out an option that enables firms to demonstrate the consideration of the",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2018"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.5",
            "summary": "The PRA expects firms to consider, and to be able to demonstrate to the PRA that they have considered:",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2018"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.6",
            "summary": "The PRA sets out an option for firms to demonstrate that they have considered the ultimate time horizon in their ORSA supervisory report using the templates and instructions set out below. This recogn",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2018"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.7",
            "summary": "Firms using the option set out above are expected to:",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2018"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.8",
            "summary": "For clarification, ultimate time horizon outputs in the nonlife underwriting risk templates (reserve risk, premium risk excluding catastrophe, and catastrophe claim risk) mean modelled outputs of scen",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2018"
          }
        ]
      },
